                    <h1>FHA and VA Loans</h1>

                    <p>Best of the Government Loans</p>
                </div>
                <div id="text" style='margin-bottom:20px;'>
                    <div class="LC" id="left" style=
                    "width:46%;padding:0 10px;">
                       <p>If you have come here it is because you feel you
                        either want an FHA (Federal Housing Assistance) loan or
                        a VA (Veteran's Administration) loan. These two
                        government loans are very different from the mainstream
                        of mortgage loans in that they offer a higher sense of
                        security to the lender than most conventional mortgage
                        loans.</p>
 

                        <p>Let's start with an FHA loan and whether it is a
                        good fit for you.</p>

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p>Do you have a 620 or higher credit
                                score?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Do you have less than 5% to pay toward a
                                down payment?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Do you plan on staying in the home for a
                                long period of time, such as more than 5
                                years?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Does your loan-to-value (LTV) ratio exceed
                                90%, thus making it hard for you to refinance
                                your existing mortgage?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Is your debt-to-income (DTI) ratio 48% or
                                lower?</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <p>If you answered yes to any of these questions, an
                        FHA mortgage loan might be a good loan vehicle for your
                        purchase or refinance. Simply complete our <a
    	href="https://lightning-mortgage.ipower.com/MortgageApplication/LoanAppShort.htm">loan
                        application</a> and make sure to note under "Loan Type"
                        that you want an FHA loan.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="RC" id="right" style=
                    "width:46%;padding:0 10px;">
                        <p>Now on to a VA loan. These loans are only available
                        to anyone that has served in the armed forces and has
                        received an honorable discharge or is an active member
                        of the armed forces and will be released from active
                        duty within the next 12 months.</p>

                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <p>Do you have a 620 or lower credit score?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Do you want 100% financing?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Do you plan on staying in the home more than
                                5 years?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Is your debt-to-income (DTI) ratio 41% or
                                lower?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Do you have a Copy of Certificate of Release
                                or Discharge From Active Duty (Form DD214)?</p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>Do you have a Certificate of Eligibility for
                                Loan Guaranty Benefits (VA 26-8320)?</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <p>If you answered yes to any of these questions, a VA
                        mortgage loan might be a good loan vehicle for your
                        purchase or refinance. Simply complete our <a
    	href="https://lightning-mortgage.ipower.com/MortgageApplication/LoanAppShort.htm">loan
                        application</a> and make sure to note under "Loan Type"
                        that you want a VA loan.</p><p>We are your best source for FHA or VA financing. 
						We work with FHA and VA borrowers in all 50 states.</p>
                    </div>
                </div><!--end of 'text' div -->
